BriefDescription: This event counts operations that cause a refill of the L1I cache. See L1I_CACHE_REFILL of ARMv9 Reference Manual for more information.
This event counts operations that cause a cache access to the L1I cache. See L1I_CACHE of ARMv9 Reference Manual for more information.
This event counts L1I_CACHE caused by demand read access.
This event counts L1I_CACHE_REFILL caused by demand read access.
This event counts operations that cause a refill of the L1I cache that incurs additional latency.
This event counts L1I_CACHE caused by hardware prefetch.
This event counts L1I_CACHE_REFILL caused by hardware prefetch.
This event counts demand fetch counted by L1I_CACHE_DM_RD that hits in the Level 1 instruction cache.
This event counts access counted by L1I_CACHE that hits in the Level 1 instruction cache.
This event counts demand access counted by L1I_CACHE_HIT_RD that hits a cache line that is in the process of being loaded into the Level 1 instruction cache.
This event counts L1I_CACHE_REFILL caused by hardware prefetch or software prefetch.
This counter counts by the number of cache refills counted by L1I_CACHE_REFILL in progress on each Processor cycle.
